devdoc.details: SLA is a service level agreement contract used for service downtime compensation

changeWhitelist(address).details: external function to change the whitelist address

params._newWhitelist: the address of the new whitelist contract

params._SLONames: the names of the service level objectives in a bytes32 array
params._SLOs: an array with the service level objective addresses
params._compensationAmount: the amount of ERC20 tokens that is distributed on a breach
params._dsla: the address of the ERC20 contract used for compensations and staking
params._ipfsHash: the ipfs hash that stores extra information about the agreement
params._owner: the owner of the service level agreement
params._stake: the amount required to stake when subscribing to the agreement
params._whitelist: the address of the whitelist used for allowing users to sign the agreement

getDetails().details: external view function that returns all agreement information

params._SLOName: the name of the SLO in bytes32

getSliInterval().details: external view function that returns the sliInterval value

getWithdrawableSubscribers().details: external view function that returns all subscribers that are entitled to a compensation

isOwner().return: true if `msg.sender` is the owner of the contract.

isSubscribed(address).details: public view function to check if a given user is subscribed to the contract

params._userAddress: the address of the user to check

isSubscribed(address).return: true if _userAddress is subscribed to the contract

registerSLI(bytes32,uint256,string).details: external function to register SLI's and check them against the SLO's

params._SLOName: the name of the SLO in bytes32
params._hash: the ipfs hash with additional information
params._value: the value of the SLI to check

renounceOwnership().details: Allows the current owner to relinquish control of the contract.

revokeAgreement().details: external function to revoke the agreement

signAgreement().details: external function to sign the agreement

transferOwnership(address).details: Allows the current owner to transfer control of the contract to a newOwner.

params.newOwner: The address to transfer ownership to.

withdrawCompensation().details: external function to withdraw the entitled compensation from the contract

withdrawCompensations(address[]).details: external function to withdraw entitled compensations for an array of addresses

params._users: the array of user addresses to withdraw compensations for

renounceOwnership().notice: Renouncing to ownership will leave the contract without an owner. It will not be possible to call the functions with the `onlyOwner` modifier anymore.
